WELCOME TO OUR WINES
Dear Wine Lovers and Friends,
The now famous "60 Minutes" exposé entitled the "French
Paradox", appeared for the first time on national television in
North America 15 years ago! It is hard to believe that time
has moved on so quickly. As a result of that program, red
wine sales around the world started to increase dramatically
ana now actually outnumper white wine in many markets!
The whole premise of the show was that people living in the
South of France were eating foods high in fat and cholesterol
but that statistically they were second only to Japan in the
least incidence of heart disease. Oh yes... the French drank
wine every day and particularly red wine in that part of the
world. So the connection was made that maybe red wine
had something to do with these results.
There has been a significant amount of research conducted
over the last 15 years trying to discover the compound in red
wine that could be responsible for this paradox. This edition
of our wine program will explore some of these concepts and
give you an insight into the scientific side of things while you
sip on some of our wonderful selections.
This edition features a good mix of Old World and New World
wines - from a North Eastern Italian Chardonnay to a great
big juicy Shiraz from Australia's Victoria region. The selections
are very expressive, truly reflecting their variety, as well as
brilliantly complementing your choice of meal.
Enjoy your flight with us today and happy travels.
Salut,
Ken Chase
Winemaker and Consultant. Delta Air Lines
